                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="atlanticcharter_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">an agreement signed by <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/winston-churchill" title="Winston Churchill definition"><span class="ndv">Winston Churchill</span></a>, the British Prime Minister, and <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/franklin-d-roosevelt" title="Franklin D Roosevelt definition"><span class="ndv">Franklin D Roosevelt</span></a>, the US President, in 1941 about the rights of nations and international relations. Its main purpose was to <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/condemn#condemn_sng_1" title="condemn definition"><span class="ndv">condemn</span></a> the actions of Germany. In 1942 statements of the Atlantic Charter became part of the Declaration of the United Nations.</span></span> <span class="xrefs" hclass="xrefs" htag="span" xt="see"><span class="prefix">see also</span> <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-second-world-war" title="Second World War definition"><span class="xr-g" bord="n" dict="all" href="secondworldwar_e"><span class="xh">Second World War</span></span></a></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
